---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Who Ben Atkins is — IT by day, curious about everything else."
  orbColor="rgba(6, 182, 212, 0.15)"
>
  <header class="mb-12">
    <h1
      class="text-4xl font-bold mb-3"
      style="font-family: var(--font-display); color: var(--color-heading);"
    >
      About
    </h1>
    <p style="color: var(--color-muted);">The longer version.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="flex flex-col gap-10" style="color: var(--color-body);">

    <section>
      <h2
        class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest mb-4"
        style="color: var(--color-muted);"
      >
        The Work
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Over six years in IT support and systems administration, across high-stakes environments
        like healthcare at VUMC and financial services at LBMC. Different compliance requirements,
        different scale, same expectation that things just work. That variety has made me versatile
        and reliable under pressure.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">
        Day to day, I handle identity and access management, M365 and Azure infrastructure,
        endpoint lifecycle, hardware deployment, PowerShell automation, and compliance coordination
        (including SOC 2 audit work). I also carry a front-end development background, which means
        I build solutions when I see gaps, not just fix what's in front of me.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2
        class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest mb-4"
        style="color: var(--color-muted);"
      >
        The Interests
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Gaming is a serious hobby. My wheelhouse: Souls-likes (the harder the better),
        Metroidvanias, JRPGs, and Rocket League — which gets its own category because it's
        basically a permanent fixture in the rotation.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
        I have a Psychology degree, and that interest never went away. Mental health, human
        behavior, what makes people tick — it shapes how I approach people problems as much as
        technical ones. It's a genuine passion, not just a line on a résumé.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Indie music across the board — rock, pop, and rap. I like music that feels like it has
        something specific to say.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">
        Fantasy Football is where my competitive side fully surfaces. I have opinions, a system,
        and zero apologies.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2
        class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest mb-4"
        style="color: var(--color-muted);"
      >
        The Background
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Psychology and Business degree from the University of Tennessee. After graduating, I spent
        several years working in healthcare — which is also where I got my first real exposure to
        enterprise IT environments. That experience pushed me toward a deliberate pivot: I enrolled
        in Nashville Software School in 2017, completed a full-stack web development bootcamp, and
        and haven't looked back.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">
        Based in Nashville. Have also spent time living in Denver in the past.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="pt-2 border-t border-[#2a2a2a]">
      <div class="flex gap-5 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/Batkins44"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="hover:text-[#a78bfa] transition-colors duration-200"
        >
          GitHub
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/batkins44"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="hover:text-[#a78bfa] transition-colors duration-200"
        >
          LinkedIn
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
